Take this game without any prescription! This is a Retro-art bullet hell with a simple yet cool story: You're a princess who just graduated from healing magic school and you descend to a place called Hurtland and start to heal people, animals, mythological creatures and even Dark lords in a bullet hell combat style.

Pros:
- It has a very nice difficult increase curve, neither too much neither too little;
- Has 3 difficult settings [spoiler]And a joke difficulty if you hold the RIGHT arrow key during difficulty selection[/spoiler];
- A nice variety of enemies, each one with its specific gimmick;
- Has its fair share of secrets, the best stats possible to finish the game are 80 hearts, 6 power, 5 multi, 10 regen and 10 flasks, try getting them all, any difficulty.
- [spoiler]You can marry anyone by the end, even an empty chest[/spoiler];
- Charming soundtrack!

Cons:
- Very short once you get used to it
- Screenshots are buggy
- Due to the limitations from the engine this was made on, there won't be achievements
- Cards were planned but not implemented because it seems steam won't let they add cards to free games even though there are some free games floating around with card drops.
